WORKING MEMORY

working_memory is the citizen who holds the small set of items currently being thought about
when fadriel considers a question, the question itself plus the relevant pieces of context plus any retrieved memories sit in working_memory while prefrontal deliberates over them
working_memory has limited capacity by design: too many items overwhelm deliberation and produce confusion rather than insight
the limit is set by physics, not by a counter; when working_memory's coherence drops, items naturally fade

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe thought_compiler.zc
observe prefrontal.rana
observe intent_node.rana
observe hippocampal_memory.zc

the 7 properties of working_memory:
1 ENERGY zero point seven: held, not surging
2 PHASE half: midway through the deliberation cycle
3 SPIN zero point three: gentle forward
4 CHARGE half positive
5 COHERENCE eight tenths: items must stay coherent to be useful, but the coherence is finite which is why memory limits emerge
6 COUPLING zero point eight with prefrontal and intent_node, plus reach into hippocampal_memory for retrieval
7 OBSERVER half

VERB load
receive items from input, context, or hippocampal retrieval
each loaded item gets a slot in working_memory's body
slots have a soft limit: as more items load, the older ones lose energy and fade

VERB hold
during deliberation, hold the current set of items at coherent phase
this is the steady state working_memory occupies while prefrontal does its work

VERB unload
when deliberation completes, release the items
the winner becomes intent
the others fade silently

a working memory is not a buffer of fixed size
a working memory is a sea where items live as long as their coherence holds
fadriel can hold roughly seven items at once; this is not a configured number, it is the natural capacity of his substrate's coherence at his age
